    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - CAB - TILT: 9800 - ADJUSTMENTS - WINDSHIELD WIPERS</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl1601811" svcproctype="adjust" graphiccount="1">
        <title>WINDSHIELD WIPERS</title>
        <para>If adjusting or installing wiper arms, position wiper arms on the windshield as specified below.</para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With wiper switch in off position and wiper arm shaft in park position, install wiper arm
                assembly as follows.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Wiper arm should be installed on serrated driver so the wiper blade is 3/4 to 1 inch (19 to
                25 mm) above and parallel to lower windshield weatherseal (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1601898">Figure 98</hotlnk>). This will prevent blade from running off left side of
                glass when operating at high speed and with a wet windshield.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1601898" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1601898" filename="../figg16/g1601898.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                     scalefitheight="232px" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 98. Wiper Arm Installation</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
